External knowledge: 
- A comprehensive customer profile is a detailed collection of customer data and information that helps businesses understand their customers better and make informed decisions; 
- Engagement history refers to the interactions customers have with a business, such as phone calls, emails, and visits; 
- Financial transaction history refers to the records of all financial transactions between a customer and a business; 
- Behavioral characteristics include demographic information, buying patterns, and campaign responses.
